00:49:18.470 --> 00:49:20.700
why do you think more
universities haven't

00:49:20.700 --> 00:49:21.201
adopted it?

00:49:21.201 --> 00:49:23.575
I mean, even though it seems
like the stuff you're saying

00:49:23.575 --> 00:49:25.514
is really obvious, it's
also somewhat rare.

00:49:25.514 --> 00:49:26.430
DAVID PATTERSON: Yeah.

00:49:26.430 --> 00:49:29.430
I got that exact same
question at Berkeley.

00:49:29.430 --> 00:49:31.800
I think-- this time
I'll be less humble.

00:49:31.800 --> 00:49:36.060
You have to have somebody
who's willing to lead.

00:49:36.060 --> 00:49:38.880
For some reason, even the
wrestling-- as I'll tell you,

00:49:38.880 --> 00:49:41.520
I wrestled in high school and
college as an individual sport.

00:49:41.520 --> 00:49:43.520
I had great
wrestling coaches who

00:49:43.520 --> 00:49:47.495
realized we'd be more successful
if we bonded as a team,

00:49:47.495 --> 00:49:49.120
even though it was
an individual sport.

00:49:49.120 --> 00:49:51.250
So I had that kind of
role model going up.

00:49:51.250 --> 00:49:54.451
And so I think I'm good at
kind of organizing teams.

00:49:54.451 --> 00:49:56.700
So you have to have somebody
who's willing to do that.

00:49:56.700 --> 00:50:00.160
The institution itself,
Berkeley, told me, day one,

00:50:00.160 --> 00:50:01.440
have impact.

00:50:01.440 --> 00:50:04.220
They didn't have any problem
with multiple people working

00:50:04.220 --> 00:50:04.720
on it.

00:50:04.720 --> 00:50:06.178
When you're an
assistant professor,

00:50:06.178 --> 00:50:09.191
you make up rules, like I have
to have only solo authored

00:50:09.191 --> 00:50:09.690
papers.

00:50:09.690 --> 00:50:10.940
Otherwise, I don't get credit.

00:50:10.940 --> 00:50:12.500
But yeah, that's not true.

00:50:12.500 --> 00:50:13.960
So the institution
let it happen.

00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:15.030
I think it was helpful.

00:50:15.030 --> 00:50:17.377
But I'm a good leader of people.

00:50:17.377 --> 00:50:19.460
But there's lots of good
leaders of people around.

00:50:19.460 --> 00:50:23.250
I don't understand why
that doesn't happen more.

00:50:23.250 --> 00:50:24.955
It seems common sense.

00:50:24.955 --> 00:50:27.080
It's not like I've kept
this a secret for 40 years.

00:50:27.080 --> 00:50:29.490
I've been telling people
at lots of institutions.

00:50:29.490 --> 00:50:30.780
So I'm not sure.

